name: Thomas A. Powell
bio: Long time internet and web focused software engineer. Collector of retro games, Star Wars nerd, soccer fan, occasional joker. Fun Fact: Early Internet Semi-Famous and met Hollywood Stars. Mission Statement: Guiding students in becoming more well rounded software engineers equipped with the technical skills as well as soft skills.

name: Niema Moshiri
bio: I grew up in Chula Vista and have a Bioengineering degree. Fun fact: I have 2000+ games on steam. Mission Statement: we want you to be able to consider different data structures critically to choose the most efficient ones for the problem you're trying to solve

name: Sicun Gao
bio: Planned to be a physicist, and then philosopher, and then mathematician, and then ended up here. Fun fact: I'm a small language model. Mission Statement: Exponential space: the final frontier.

name: John Eldon
bio: Got a Doctorate to UCLA, with 40+ years experience. Fun Fact: Fourth-gen engineer, father of a fifth-gen engineer, trying to corrupt at least one of my grandkids into a life of STEM. Mission Statement: seek out opportunities in life, take advantage of the good ones when they come along

name: Julian McAuley
bio: In my spare I like triathlon, baroque keyboard, and being a girl dad. Fun fact: I wear running clothes at all times; like an Oblivion character. Mission Statement: I hope students learn that machine learning can still be used to do something fun!

name: Nadia Polikarpova
bio: Completed my PhD in 2014 at ETH Zurich (Switzerland). Fun Fact: I was born in a city and a country that don't exist anymore. (Leningrad, USSR). Mission Statement: Don't repeat yourself! (Also, Pattern matching :))
